</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uaishen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aishen</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 1114<br> <font color=#E9D756>(8/2/02 5:28:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10267.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fair Ways to Distribute Guild Loot</span><hr size=1> We work off allocation and I'll agree that it's a dangerous system to work with, but the people who can't handle it tend to weed themselves out and move on.  Seriously, though, every system will rely on officers' judgement calls.  Whether it's the decision to award a guildie points, allow a guildie to random for the loot, or award a guildie the loot straight off, it still comes down to the judgement call.  Good officers will make good judgement no matter what system, and the questionable ones will manage to piss people off no matter what system they're using to handle it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/userien.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Serien</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 76<br> <font color=#E9D756>(8/2/02 5:48:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10267.topic&index=7>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fair Ways to Distribute Guild Loot</span><hr size=1> Points systems based on raid attendance have an inherent assumption ... that a persons value to the guild is shown through raiding, hence they get rewarded for it.  For guilds that have a membership that enjoys focusing on raiding, this works well.<br>
<br>
For guilds that do not do much raiding, determining participation in the guild becomes much more subjective and not something that is easy to fit into a points scheme. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ucaelie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Caelie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 84<br> <font color=#E9D756>(8/2/02 6:13:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10267.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fair Ways to Distribute Guild Loot</span><hr size=1> Thanks Serien for clearing that up. I have always been in the more casual guilds and always opposed the point system.<br>
<br>
For instance, we raid every Friday night. If your online you need to be at the raid. Thats great and we usually have a pretty good turnout. Then you have those that work weekends or are on a totally different time zone and not able to attend the Friday night raid. Lets say these guildmembers may not be able to attend the raids due to RL interference, but when they are online they are a real value to the guild, always helping others and just a down right good guild member. With the point system lets say this member was on vacation and able to attend the raid. Woohoo, but he would be left out at the chance of a nice item.<br>
<br>
